description: Reconnect and secure the previously identified floating positive input cable of Control Module 6 to the positive output terminal of Control Module 5, restoring electrical continuity of the 12V line between these modules., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Module 6 input cabling and connectors,
description: Inspect and manually trace the two-cable pair between Control Module 5 and Control Module 6, ensuring that both the positive and negative cables from CM5’s output are firmly plugged into CM6’s corresponding input terminals and that no connector remains floating or partially inserted., outcome='Control Output Cable (+) 5 is correctly tied to Control Input Cable (+) 6, but Control Input Cable (+) 6’s negative port is floating/disconnected. Control Output Cable (−) 5 is connected to Control Input Cable (−) 6, with no polarity inversion detected on the negative pair.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control Module 6 internal circuit and indicator LED,
description: Open the inspection panel of Control Module 6 and visually check the internal wiring of the switch, series LED/resistor branch, and both positive/negative terminals of the cable pair. Confirm whether the positive input, positive output, negative input, and negative output nodes are all correctly soldered/connected to the PCB traces and that the red indicator LED and its resistor are intact and properly oriented., outcome='The enclosure for Control Cube 6 could not be opened, but inverting it allowed internal visual inspection. All four Control 6 cables show as connected with no observable internal faults; no polarity inversion is explicitly indicated by the available data. The green power flow indicator LED 6 and its series resistor 6 are both missing and cannot be replaced.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load module (lamp and series diode),
description: With all switches ON and the current cabling left as-is, use a continuity tester (unpowered) across the two external load-module terminals, then between each terminal and the internal lamp/indicator/diode nodes if accessible, to determine whether there is an open circuit or failed diode/lamp inside the load module that would prevent current flow even with correct upstream wiring., outcome='Continuity testing could not be performed on the load cables, internal bulb, or diode because a multimeter/continuity tester is unavailable. The load cube enclosure has been inverted, providing visual access inside, but no internal electrical diagnostics were completed.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> All control-module and load-module indicators and main lamp,
description: With a good 12V battery installed and all switches set to ON, visually inspect the top of each control module (1–8) and the load module to confirm which, if any, red switch-indicator LEDs are physically present in their holders and whether the main lamp and the internal load indicator lamp are present and appear intact (not obviously broken or missing). Report a list of modules with missing or visibly damaged LEDs/lamps., outcome='All eight control-module switches (1–8) appear present, closed, and without observable internal faults; no missing or visibly damaged red switch-indicator LEDs were reported.  \nThe main load lamp and the internal indicator lamp are both present, appear intact, and show no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=205.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
